That&#39;s only true of a simple dipole.  Antennas can be engineered to get &lt;br&gt;
practically any pattern you want. In fact, many FM and TV antennas have a &lt;br&gt;
pattern which peaks from directly below the antenna to the horizon and &lt;br&gt;
sends very little signal straight up.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
Also, close-in you might still be in the Fresnel zone of the field.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
Zack&lt;br&gt;
